                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18460921-1982-offence-1 t18460921-name-1187"></join>Henry John Wharton</persName>, and another.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460921-name-1188" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1188" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1188" type="surname" value="STACEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1188" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY STACEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Henry John Wharton, and another, pawnbrokers, at Newington—causeway. I missed a coat on the evening of the 14th of Sept.—I have not seen it</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460921-name-1189" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1189" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1189" type="surname" value="KEARLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460921-name-1189" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES KEARLEY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant P</hi> 36.) I saw the prisoner steal the coat, on Monday night, the 14th of Sept., at a quarter before nine o'clock—I had watched him for a quarter of an hour before—I was in plain clothes—I was looking at him very minutely—I could not take him on account of so many persons being in the road—it was the Surrey Zoological Gardens night, and I could not get across—I know it was him—I had watched him three nights—he had some difficulty in getting the coat off the blind—he took it with two hands.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. MELLER</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You were watching? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—he had another with him—there were very few persons between me and the shop; but I could not take the prisoner, it was done so quick—an omnibus stopped opposite a dark turning, and I was on the opposite side—I just turned into the road, and there I missed him, the crowd was so great—there was not a crowd at the shop—I did not cry "Stop thief!"</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18460921-1982-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
